# agents.conf — roster of agent-ids for the orchestration scripts.
#
# Copy this file to "$CLAUDE_LAB/agents.conf" (default: ~/.claude-lab/agents.conf)
# and list one agent-id per line. The orchestration scripts read it via
# lib/agents.sh (list_agents).
#
# Rules:
#   - One agent-id per line.
#   - Blank lines are ignored.
#   - Everything after a '#' on a line is treated as a comment and ignored.
#
# If this file is absent, list_agents() falls back to scanning
# "$CLAUDE_LAB"/*/.claude and using each parent directory name as an agent-id
# (excluding shared, logs, mcp-servers, __pycache__).
#
# Example:
# agent-one
# agent-two
# agent-three
